            "answer_text": "As always, the question determines the answer. If the intent of the question was to ask what fraction of Nazi Germany\u2019s war effort was E Front, then the answer would be different. War effort includes not just army manpower, but economic effort, air force, navy, and home defense [flak, fire department, etc.]. Essentially all of the German naval effort was against the West. Most of the air force was tied down either campaigning in the West (early on) or defending the homeland (later in the war), with only a brief interval in 1941 when it was mostly committed in the East. Homeland defense included large numbers of flak installations. These were stripped, right before the end, and sent to the Oder front to shore up the anti-tank defenses of this last river before Berlin. To no avail, of course, because by that time the Soviets had overrun Silesia and the Americans had surrounded and then captured the Ruhr and the British were overrunning the North German plain so ammo ran out. ",
